DJ and producer Citi Lyts has died, leaving his fans and the South African hip hop fraternity heartbroken. A family friend, who didn’t want to be named, confirmed to Daily Sun that he has died. “He has passed on, but details about his death are still sketchy,” said the friend. Another source, who is a friend of the late musician, said Citi Lyts (32), whose real name was Sandile Mkhize, was shot dead during a robbery in the early hours of Monday, 14 February. The DJ became popular in 2015 with his single Washa when he joined record label Ambitiouz Entertainment. From there, he released more singles with musicians like Fifi Cooper, Sjava, B3nchmarq, Lasauce and Emtee. ALSO READ : NEW DOOR OPENS FOR NELISA! His brother, Prokid, died in 2018 after having suffered a severe seizure. A few months after that, Citi Lyts dedicated a song titled Cel’Ukuthi to him. Since the news of his passing broke, tributes have been pouring in for him on social media. Rapper Touchline thanked Citi Lyts for believing in him. “Farewell my brother?? Thank you for believing in me. Citi Lyts Forever,” he said. Slikour On Life tweeted: “Sad day… Rest in power DJ Citi Lyts.” Singer Donald said he was hurt by Citi Lyt’s passing. “RIP Citi Lyts, one of the realest brothers I’ve ever met. This one hurts really deep. Till we meet again my G,” he wrote. Farewell my brother?? Thank you for believing in me. Citi Lyts Forever Sad day… Rest In Power DJ Citi Lyts ???? The South African Hip Hop fraternity mourns the death of DJ Sandile “DJ Citi Lyts” Mkhize. Our heartfelt condolences goes out to the family, friends and fans #RIPDJCitiLyts ????? pic.twitter.com/jG71wuNYuN 